sentence: In consumer sector news, Brinker International ( EAT ) reported fiscal Q3 earnings per diluted share, excluding special items, increased 16.7% to $0.84 compared to $0.72 for the third quarter of fiscal 2013.
Results beat analyst estimates of $0.83 EPS.
Company sales increased 2% to $739.2 million, up from $724.69 in Q3 of fiscal 2013 but lower than analyst predictions of $766.2 million.
Shares of EAT are down 0.44 or 0.85% in pre-market trading at $51.23 with a 52-week range of $36.52-$55.45.

And, Delta Airlines ( DAL ) shares are up more than 2% pre-bell Wednesday after the airline said Q1 adjusted profit and sales gained, despite severe winter weather that caused the cancellation of more than 17,000 flights.
Earnings were $281 million, or $0.33 per diluted share, from $85 million, or $0.10 a year ago, beating analysts estimates for $0.29, according to Capital IQ.
The airline said on a GAAP basis its net income was $213 million, or $0.25 a share from $7 million or $0.01 a year ago.
Finally, Procter & Gamble ( PG ) reported Q3 core earnings per share of $1.04, beating analyst estimates of $1.01 and representing an increase of 5% versus 2013.
Total revenues were unchanged versus the prior year at $20.6 billion in the quarter, in line with analyst estimates.
Shares of PG were down 0.52 or 0.6% at $80.74 in pre-market trading with a 52-week range of $73.61-$85.82.
